1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the performance of optical fiber systems and proposes digital processing techniques to increase spectral efficiency, which falls under the scope of information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with the transmission of data over optical fiber systems, which is a networking and internet architecture-related topic. 
3. cs.OH (Other Computer Science): The paper may fall under this category as it does not fit into any specific sub-category of computer science. 
4. cs.PF (Performance): The paper discusses the performance of optical fiber systems and proposes techniques to improve it, which falls under the scope of performance evaluation. 
5. cs.SI (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the control of optical fiber systems to avoid burst interaction and improve performance, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
